thread.title: Retail spending to stay solid

title: Retail spending to stay solid
text:
View Photo 

New retail spending figures are expected to show a third straight month of stronger activity at the cash register. 
Retail sales are expected to have risen 0.4 per cent in July, though that will be slower than June's 0.7 gain, which was the strongest monthly growth since February. 
Westpac economists expect there will be a fall from June, when business spending spiked on the federal budget's increased tax rebate. 
July spending may also be dragged down by the impact on consumer confidence of sharp falls on China's share market, and the uncertainty caused by the Greek debt crisis. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Retail spending to stay solid AAP
